Author: MJCoin Project
Title: [ANN] MJCoin - Changing the cannabis market forever
Body: Thank you for your comment!  Your concern is understandable, and we expect others share your perspective.  Recent events have focused attention on the legalization of recreational cannabis at the US Federal level, and Canada is on track to legalize it near mid 2018. Regardless of the exact dates and policy changes, it is widely acknowledged that the production and sale of cannabis should be keenly regulated and tracked, which is exactly what the MJCoin Project is about.  We want to bring the inherent trust and immutability of blockchain to an industry that will thrive with such a framework.  Here are a couple of recent articles for some quick reading on the subject. Enjoy! https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-01-02/canada-pot-stocks-start-2018-with-a-bang-as-california-legalizes https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2018/01/05/marijuana-sellers-undeterred-threat-federal-prosecution/1008483001/

Author: MJCoin Project
Title: [ANN] MJCoin - Changing the cannabis market forever
Body: MJCoin Changing the cannabis market forever   https://mjcoin.com  http://mjcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MJCoin.png  http://mjcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/slider.png   WHITE PAPER   https://mjcoin.com/white-paper    The future is here A completely legal way of allowing people to pay for their legal cannabis products without using a credit or debit card.    MJCoin Highlights  Decentralized Decentralization serves as a democratic safe guard against corruption, censorship, inflation and the invasion of privacy. MJCoin is managed by its network, and not any one central authority.  Private Privacy is a delicate subject for cryptocurrencies and the payment industry in general. MJCoin implements a protocol which provides a higher degree of privacy over other cryptocurrencies.  Fast One of the key requirements to creating a coin is the confirmation time. Speed is one feature where MJCoin really shines. Transfers can be confirmed within seconds.  Safe In addition to standard security features inherited from its predecessors, MJCoin implements several enhancements from which users benefit making it super secure.   MJCoin Team  Jeremy Christianson - CO-FOUNDER / VP  Jeremy brings an entrepreneurial and leadership background from within a multitude of industries beginning his career as an entrepreneur straight out of high school having owned/operated a successful graphics business. While going on having gained experience in different industries including Law Enforcement, IT, etc. he recognized the shortfalls all industries were experiencing with IT.  He obtained a degree in Computer Science and Network Administration and dived into the IT industry leading a multitude of technical teams and projects, and learned the details of the shortfalls the industry is experiencing. Jeremy then formed Heuristics IT Engineering where he carefully organized a team of experts and together have successfully developed a series of refreshed business models the IT industry desperately needs to adequately interact/support today’s fast-paced and ever-evolving world for years to come. Time away includes traveling with the family throughout the US, spending time on the beach/oceans around the coasts, deep sea fishing, and keeping up with the latest in the exotic auto market.   Jeshua Watley - LEAD TECHNICAL ENGINEER  Jeshua Watley is the Lead Technical Engineer. He is responsible for presenting technical outlines to other team members, communicating with professional resources, and administrating details for key projects and implementations.  Jeshua earned a Bachelor of Science in Computer Network Management at age 20 and is a career IT professional with broad experience in multiple technologies. Jeshua likes to keep his mind active with games of all kinds, and he is an avid movie-goer.   Paul Marinsky - LEAD INFORMATION SECURITY ENGINEER  Paul Marinsky brings to us a wealth of knowledge derived from a multi-discipline background in both law enforcement and information security. As our Lead Information Security Engineer, he is responsible for evaluating and developing solutions to mitigate risk to information assets.  He holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Criminal Justice and an AAS in Network Management and Cyber Security. He is network and security certified and holds a specialized certification as a Digital Forensics Examiner. As an avid traveler, storm chasing, scuba diving, and photography consume much of his time away from the technical world.   Chris Wingard - DATABASE ARCHITECH / DEVELOPER  More info soon.    You can follow us at  https://twitter.com/MJCoinProject https://www.facebook.com/MJCoinProject/ https://t.me/MJCoin     We are working hard to update this thread as fast as we can. We will be adding whitepaper and team info asap.  Open to suggestions!

Author: MJCoin Project
Title: [ANN] MJCoin - Changing the cannabis market forever
Body: Thank you for your questions and continued interest in MJCoin.  1. MJCoin, Inc. is a US based company.  Medical and recreational cannabis legislation is being added to many States.  However, MJCoin is looking to service the legal cannabis industry inside and outside the US. 2. We have spent the last year working and speaking with members of the legal cannabis professional community, which is why the MJCoin is being presented and why we believe there is a need for such a project. 3. Although medical and recreational cannabis usage is becoming more acceptable in the US and abroad, the legal cannabis industry is still vastly under-serviced. We feel very strongly that the MJCoin Project can provide a valuable service to consumers and businesses, large and small. The MJCoin Project will develop a blockchain that will help the industry track its orders, growing and shipping processes, and more, while using the mining token as a reward for miners to maintain the data and as an active currency for the market.
